HEADWORD: Hypocycloid
<hw>Hy`po*cy"cloid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>hypo-</ets> + <ets>cycloid</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>hypocyclo⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A curve
traced by a point in the circumference of a circle which rolls on the
concave side in the fixed circle. Cf. <er>Epicycloid</er>, and
<er>Trochoid</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

